<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-220-248 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 392 014</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 18 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for PC: Tricom announces business communicator kit. (TricomCommunications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tricom Communications Ltd. (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyCommunications softwareModemsUnited Kingdom.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR PC: Tricom Announces Business Communicator Kit 02/18/91 HIGH WYCOMBE,BUCKS, ENGLAND, 1991 FEB 18 (NB) -- Tricom Communications, which secured thecontract to supply a modem plus communications software to IBM for inclusionin the PS/1 computer kit, has begun selling the same bundle for use with anyPC compatible machine.andM;The package, consisting of a Tricom Quad modem and British Telecom's DialcomCommunicator communications software, is billed as a &quot;plug in and go&quot; kitthat allows PC users to access a variety of line services, such as BT'sPrestel and Telecom Gold services, and many others.andM;&quot;Given that the concept behind the PC is to provide a product for use by thesmaller businessman, the simple addition of the Tricom modem will allow thesmaller business to share in the much larger network resources supplied byBritish Telecom and other organisations,&quot; said Mike Hafferty, Tricom'schairman, announcing the availability of the package.andM;&quot;With the introduction of this truly affordable modem, Tricom has opened upthe world of data communication and the business benefits offered bytechnology to a wider marketplace,&quot; he added.andM;The Tricom modem works to all modems speeds to 2400 bits per second (bps) andincludes V.42, V.42Bis and MNP Class 5 error correction and data compressionas a standard feature.andM;Dialcom Communicator, meanwhile, is a semi-automated communications packagethat support both viewdata and scrolling ASCII data formats.andP;  The packageruns on most PCs.andM;Interestingly, Tricom is selling the Business Communicator package throughbusiness dealers throughout the UK, leaving it up to the dealer to setpricing.andP;  According to Hafferty, the package will be sold at an affordableprice.andM;&quot;We firmly believe that there is a large untapped market for modem productswithin the small to medium sized business community and Tricom will beundertaking a substantial marketing programme to promote the benefits of theof the `might modem.andP;  throughout all sectors of the business community,&quot; hesaid.andM;(Steve Gold/19910218/Press andamp; Public Contact: Tricom Communications - Tel:0494-483951)</TEXT></DOC>